That our greatest strengths are the ideals we share.

name: Slotkin, Elissa
message:
But what I also remember so vividly after 9/11 was the way the country came together in the months after the attacks. 

We were united in respecting the sacrifice of the first responders, and in answering the call to come together as Americans.

name: Slotkin, Elissa
message:
Each year, we mark 9/11 by remembering those who were lost. It was a generational event.

But this year, we mark this day in the middle of yet another generational event, the COVID-19 crisis.

We were not the same country after 9/11 –– and it may be quite the same with COVID.

name: Slotkin, Elissa
message: Our country was forever changed by those events, as was my life. This day, 19 years ago, was what started my career in national security. A year later, I was recruited by the CIA to be a Middle East analyst.

name: Slotkin, Elissa
message:
Nineteen years ago today, I was in New York City, on my second day of grad school, when 9/11 took place.

I remember the fear, the sounds of sirens headed downtown, the F-16s that flew overhead, and later, the sound of the bagpipes accompanying the remains of first responders.

name: Levin, Andy
message: The pandemic is worsening every day. The need for substantial change grows every day. It’s time to rebuild our public health systems. It’s time to transform our economy into a sustainable, equitable, 21st century powerhouse.

name: Levin, Andy
message: With all the noise and controversy over the nomination of Amy Coney Barrett, it’s easy to lose sight of the truth: health care is a human right. We cannot be an equal society until every American has access to health care.

name: Levin, Andy
message: RT If you’re paying way too much for prescription drugs…in the middle of a public health crisis.

name: Levin, Andy

name: Levin, Andy
message: Can you believe we are marking two years since the shooting at the Tree of Life Synagogue in Pittsburgh? I am still reeling from this murderous act of anti-Semitism. But know this: our Jewish community won't be deterred in our fight against hatred of Jews & all forms of bigotry.

name: Levin, Andy
message: My office is seeking community judges for the annual Congressional App Challenge. College students or professionals from my district with an interest in judging should contact my office at (586)-498-7122. For information about the challenge, visit https://t.co/DlAP56X2fw.

name: Levin, Andy
message: Congratulations to the Michigan health care workers who won these well-deserved raises. I am fighting to make sure essential workers are both celebrated and fairly compensated for their work during the COVID-19 pandemic. https://t.co/eaMS71YeIk

name: Levin, Andy
message: The lack of a national response to the pandemic has put our schools in such a poor position that teachers may be leaving the profession to avoid COVID. Our children can’t afford another shock to their education. Congress needs to help schools now. https://t.co/KEMpDwyV55

name: Levin, Andy
message: The record COVID case numbers we’ve seen over the past week are a clear sign we need a national testing and tracing strategy like the one I outlined fully five months ago in my Coronavirus Containment Corps Act.

name: Levin, Andy
message: The consequences of Republican’s inaction on COVID relief are painfully visible. We should be sending our universities the funding needed to cover shortfalls caused by the pandemic. Idly watching schools slash programs and faculty is a dereliction of Congress’s duty.

name: Levin, Andy
message: Let it mark a low point, and not a new normal, in our democratic process. 13//

name: Levin, Andy
message: This nomination will be remembered as a mistake, as the power-hungry flailing of an increasingly authoritarian Republican Party. I condemn the Senate’s confirmation. 12/

name: Levin, Andy
message: The Senate GOP and the White House have ignored Americans’ voices, but they cannot ignore Americans’ votes. 11/

name: Levin, Andy
message: It’s clear that voters nationwide believed this seat should have been filled by the winner of the presidential election, and voters in Michigan both agree with upholding these norms and support the Affordable Care Act. 10/

name: Levin, Andy
message: As families continue to grapple with this once-in-a-lifetime health emergency, GOP senators have jeopardized the health care of millions. 9/

name: Levin, Andy
message: Insurance companies will no longer be required to cover essential preventative services like annual checkups and flu shots. What has our country come to? 8/

name: Levin, Andy
message: If a far-right Supreme Court declares the Affordable Care Act unconstitutional, 20 million Americans stand to lose their health insurance immediately, and folks with preexisting condition will lose protections, including more than 4 million Michiganders. 7/

name: Levin, Andy
message: This confirmation puts the health and well-being of Americans at risk. 6/

name: Levin, Andy
message: This rushed confirmation is an assault on democracy that sets a dangerous precedent for future Supreme Court nominations. 5/

name: Levin, Andy
message: With more than 58 million votes already cast in next week’s election, all pretense offered by Republican leaders that this nomination represents the will of the people has fallen away. 4/

name: Levin, Andy
message: Coney Barret joins Neil Gorsuch and Brett Kavanaugh as the only justices in history to have been nominated by a president who did not win a majority of the votes and confirmed by senators who do not represent a majority of Americans. 3/

name: Levin, Andy
message: The Senate’s vote yesterday confirms what we already knew: Majority Leader McConnell and Republican senators will sacrifice norms, their own stated principles and the democratic process to pack the court with judges who share their ideological beliefs. 2/

name: Levin, Andy
message: Thoughts on the Amy Coney Barrett nomination 1/

message:

message: Even Trump’s own appointee agrees. https://t.co/8NIEpmpQo3

name: Levin, Andy
message: Congress has the tools to mount an effective public health and economic response to the COVID-19 pandemic, and I will not stop fighting to see it carried out. 11/

name: Levin, Andy
message: I implore my colleagues in the Senate to stop racing to install a justice onto the Supreme Court in order to strike down the Affordable Care Act and destroy life-saving protections for people with pre-existing conditions, and instead focus on relief for the American people. 10/

name: Levin, Andy
message: The unemployment, the lack of child care, the inability of people to work with adequate safety measures, the lack of nationwide testing and contact tracing—all of it points to the dire need for comprehensive relief from Congress and the president. 9/

name: Levin, Andy
message: We know that neither of the twin public health and economic crises we face will go away without a comprehensive government response. In fact, both crises are likely to worsen as we enter the winter months. 8/

name: Levin, Andy
message: Director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention Robert Redfield has said we face, ‘the worst fall, from a public health perspective, we’ve ever had.’ 7/

name: Levin, Andy
message: Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell has said that, ‘The recovery will be stronger and move faster if monetary policy and fiscal policy continue to work side by side to provide support to the economy until it is clearly out of the woods.’ 6/

name: Levin, Andy
message: Meanwhile Trump’s own appointees are voicing their full support for additional relief and public health experts are warning of severe consequences if we do not change course. 5/

name: Levin, Andy
message: Speaker Pelosi has been ready to strike a deal that rushes aid to the American people for months and has made meaningful efforts to bridge the partisan divide, even going so far as to update the Heroes Act in October. 4/

name: Levin, Andy
message: Coming into lowering temperatures that move Americans indoors, in the biggest public health crisis in a century, the president and the Congress have one job: send comprehensive relief to the American people. 3/

name: Levin, Andy
message: It is clear from the votes last week that Senate Republicans haven’t moved beyond the cynicism preventing them from actually negotiating a COVID relief bill with Democrats, but there is still time to act. 2/

name: Meijer, Peter
message: The #AbrahamAccords succeeded by ditching beltway groupthink divorced from zero-sum reality, and accepting as a starting point dynamics as they are. Our global engagement would be far better served with honesty & humility, rather than the arrogance of groundless expertise. (5/5)

name: Meijer, Peter
message: We understood our world through narrative, condensed frameworks that are imbued with biases and wish-fulfillment. I think of it like a cookie-cutter; you can’t deny the dough outside the edges is there. Indeed, there is a lot to learn from what’s left out. (4/5)

name: Meijer, Peter
message:
Too many reports & studies are written by experts who read other reports & studies written by experts who read other reports & studies. 

This kind of knowledge can be a trap, divorced from consequence, high on trivia. Danger lies in believing the studied world is reality. (3/5)

name: Meijer, Peter
message: Pulling no punches, @Doranimated highlights what I felt often as a conflict analyst: the gulf between aloof expert consensus (that invariably trended towards some illusory, halcyon ideal) and what it was like on the ground, dealing with real people suffering reality. (2/5)

name: Jon Hoadley
message:
The homophobia & vitriol we’ve seen as we’ve become more and more competitive only makes me more grounded in my commitment to serve as a leadership example for other LGBTQ+ folks. 

It’s hard to be what you can’t see - this path hasn’t been easy, but it’s certainly been worth it.

name: Jon Hoadley
message:
On this #NationalComingOutDay , I’ve come a long way since that day on my dad’s John Deere in 1996. 

This year, I have the opportunity to make history as the first ever LGBTQ+ Member of Congress from Michigan, though it certainly hasn’t been easy.

name: Jon Hoadley
message: We currently have Supreme Court justices and a Republican Party calling for equality back on the chopping block once again. This campaign is historic in and of itself, but putting leaders who look like ourselves in office is how we make true progress.

name: Jon Hoadley
message:
Today, I’m the Democratic nominee for Congress in a district where a Democrat hasn’t held the seat in over three decades. 

Running for #MI06 seemed like a moonshot, but nothing worthwhile is ever easy. And now, we’re winning this race.

name: Jon Hoadley
message:
Sometimes it felt like I was right back to riding that lawnmower in South Dakota.

Our community is far from the days of living in the shadows, but to fully take our place in the sun means bringing visibility and evolution to the complexities of our lives.

name: Jon Hoadley
message:
I got my start in public service advocating to make marriage equality the law of the land (before it was cool).

When I first ran for State Rep, it seemed I was too young, too gay, and too “not from here." I don’t remember its origin, but it's the story I started telling myself.

name: Jon Hoadley
message:
Coming out to others happened in stages. A crush on a guy from the tennis team turning into my first boyfriend. 

My first boyfriend turned into a question from my sister while she was brushing her teeth: 

“Are you dating a guy on the tennis team?” “Yes. Pass the toothpaste.”

name: Jon Hoadley
message:
I was a gay kid growing up in South Dakota who said the words, “I’m gay” for the first time while riding my dad’s John Deere so no one would hear me. 

13-year-old me back in 1996 couldn’t dream of a world where our lives and our love would be part of the American conversation.
